課程概述 Course Description
       This course is design mainly for graduate law students who have taken the basic courses of Corporations and Securities Regulation.  This course serves as advanced inquiries to the general framework as well as contemporary issues of the law of corporations.  It also provides an good review of various areas of business law.  It further furnishes advanced discussions of law and practices in selected areas of mergers and acquisitions.  After the course of study, students will be expect to gain broader and deeper understandings of merger and acquisition law, to develop their abilities to apply merger and acquisition law against any given factual circumstance, and to utilize their knowledge and understandings in their future disciplines. 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    Students will be expect to gain broader and deeper understandings of merger and acquisition law.
Students will be able to develop their abilities to apply merger and acquisition law against any given factual circumstance.
Students will be able to utilize their knowledge and understandings in their future disciplines.    

